The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms with deep neural networks for playing Atari games, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also focuses on optimization methods for deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of optimization and control. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses computer vision techniques for processing game images, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of optimization methods for control, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
